text.tspan: Test driven development (TDD) is a process where tests are
written before the code. you start by writing a small test, after
you create enough code for the test to pass.
Then you write another test and rinse and repeat, this allows the
testability of the code to be built into the software itself.
TDD can be implemented into our project in many different
I believe that one of the best ways to implement this would be
to create a shared document where we can break up all the
features of the site and create tests for each section.
This will also allow for us to create a development timeline to
keep track of our progress and what still needs to be
implemented and tested with our site.
